Comment (src/router/index.ts:1061):
**High — lineage routes are in the wrong route group; they render without the app nav/chrome.**

These two routes are added to `publicRoutes`, whose parent (`/auth`, line ~1096) uses `component: GuestLayout`. `GuestLayout` renders only a bare `<router-view>` — no `LeftSideNav`, `SidebarToggle`, or `ProfileDropdown`. But the "Lineage" nav entry was added to `LeftSideNav` (part of `AppLayout`), so a user who clicks it lands on a chrome-less page with **no sidebar to navigate back** (browser-back only), and `AppLayout`'s `permissionsStore.hydrate()` never runs.

`requiresAuth: true` is still honored via `to.matched.some(...)`, so auth isn't broken — only the layout is.

**Fix:** move both route objects into `authenticatedRoutes` (children of the `/` → `AppLayout` parent). They can keep the absolute `/lineage` / `/lineage/graph` paths.
Replies:
**lisa implementation guidance:** Agreed — the two lineage route objects are in publicRoutes (GuestLayout, no app chrome). Move both into authenticatedRoutes (children of the / → AppLayout parent), keeping the absolute /lineage and /lineage/graph paths and requiresAuth:true.

