Comment (src/components/lineage/LineageNodeDrawer.vue:104):
**Low — evidence fetch has no request-race guard.**

This watcher re-runs `loadEvidence` on every `node.key` change. Two rapid node switches race, and whichever response resolves last wins — so node A's evidence can end up displayed under node B. A per-request token (capture the key, ignore the response if `props.node?.key` changed by the time it resolves) would harden it. Nit-level for a PoC.
Replies:
**lisa implementation guidance:** Agreed. Add a per-request token guard to loadEvidence: capture node.key at call time and ignore the response if props.node?.key has changed by the time it resolves.

